X Platform - Public Website Architecture & UI Refactoring Documentation
Project Overview

This phase focused on improving the public-facing section of X Platform.

The goal was not to introduce new backend systems, but to improve frontend architecture, remove duplicated components, create reusable layout structures, improve maintainability, and prepare the platform for future scalability.

The work completed during this phase included:

Public Navbar Architecture
Shared Navigation System
Public Footer System
Public Pages Refactoring
Dynamic User Navigation
Profile Synchronization
Content Strategy Improvements
Translation Architecture Planning
Responsive Design Preparation
Frontend Maintainability Improvements
Public Website Architecture
Purpose

The public website was originally built with duplicated navigation structures across multiple pages.

Each page contained its own navbar implementation, resulting in:

Repeated code
Harder maintenance
Slower UI updates
Increased risk of inconsistencies

The architecture was redesigned to use shared reusable components.

Public Navbar System
Overview

A dedicated public navigation component was created.

File:

src/components/layout/PublicNavbar.tsx

Purpose:

Provide a single navigation component shared across all public pages.

Navbar Responsibilities

The Public Navbar now handles:

User authentication state
Profile image rendering
Username rendering
Dynamic dashboard navigation
Login navigation
Logout functionality
Public page navigation
Dynamic User Rendering

The navbar automatically reads user data from:

localStorage

Displayed information:

Username
Profile image
Authentication status
Profile Image System

The navbar automatically displays:

User uploaded profile image

Fallback:

Default avatar icon
Dynamic Dashboard Navigation

The navbar supports role-based navigation.

Rules:

Admin
→ Admin Dashboard
Teacher
→ Teacher Dashboard
Student
→ Student Dashboard
Logout System

The logout functionality was centralized inside the Public Navbar.

Responsibilities:

Remove local storage session data
Redirect user
Update UI state
